In the Apple SSL bug, a goto statement works much like a function call or a throw in Java.  Here&#x27;s a Java example that compiles without warning and has the same flaw:<p><pre><code>    public static void foo() throws Exception {
        throw new Exception();
    }

    public static int bar() throws Exception {
        int x = 0;
        if(x == 1)
            foo();		
            foo();
        x++;
        return x;
    }</code></pre>

I use ADT as well, and IIRC there <i>are</i> certain kinds of unreachable code that won&#x27;t compile:<p><pre><code>  public int foo(int i) {
      return 2;

      return i;
  }</code></pre>
